DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Primary Tumor Lower Uterus Segment Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The original tumor._Lower; the bottom one of two._The hollow muscular organ in which the impregnated ovum is developed into the child; it is about 7.5 cm in length in the nonpregnant woman, and consists of a main portion (body) with an elongated lower part (neck), at the extremity of which is the opening (os). The upper rounded portion of the uterus, opposite the os, is the fundus, at each extremity of which is the horn marking the part where the uterine tube joins the uterus and through which the ovum reaches the uterine cavity after leaving the ovary. The organ is supported in the pelvic cavity by the broad ligaments, round ligaments, cardinal ligaments, and rectouterine and vesicouterine folds or ligaments. SYN metra, womb._One of the parts into which something naturally divides._An event, entity or condition that typically characterizes a prescribed environment or situation and determines or aids in determining whether certain stated circumstances exist or criteria are satisfied.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Chemotherapy Temozolomide Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator whether there was prior administration of temozolomide (A triazene analog of dacarbazine with antineoplastic activity.  As a cytotoxic alkylating agent, temozolomide is converted at physiologic pH to the short-lived active compound, monomethyl triazeno imidazole carboxamide (MTIC). The cytotoxicity of MTIC is due primarily to methylation of DNA at the O6 and N7 positions of guanine, resulting in inhibition of  DNA replication.  Unlike dacarbazine, which is metabolized to MITC only in the liver, temozolomide is metabolized to MITC at all sites. Temozolomide is administered orally and penetrates well into the central nervous system. (NCI04))

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Chemotherapy Dacarbazine Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: the yes/no indicator whether there was prior administration of DTIC (A triazene derivative with antineoplastic activity. Dacarbazine alkylates and cross-links DNA during all phases of the cell cycle, resulting in disruption of DNA function, cell cycle arrest, and apoptosis. (NCI04)_The act of having given something (e.g., a medication or test).)

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Chemotherapy Capecitabine Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: the yes/no indicator whether there was prior administration of Capecitabine (a fluoropyrimidine carbamate belonging to the class of antineoplastic agents called antimetabolites.  As a prodrug, capecitabine is selectively activated by tumor cells to its cytotoxic moiety, 5-fluorouracil (5-FU); subsequently, 5-FU is metabolized to two active metabolites, 5-fluoro-2-deoxyuridine monophosphate (FdUMP) and 5-fluorouridine triphosphate (FUTP) by both tumor cells and normal cells.  FdUMP inhibits DNA synthesis and cell division by reducing normal thymidine production, while FUTP inhibits RNA and protein synthesis by competing with uridine triphosphate. (NCI04))

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Mantle Cell Lymphoma International Prognostic Index Combined Biologic Index Risk Assessment Category
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to estimate a patient's risk of mantle cell lymphoma progression or relapse and overall survival following therapy using a scoring system. It uses the criteria of patient's age, ECOG performance status, serum LDH activity, WBC count and Ki-67 index to classify patients into low risk, medium risk or high risk groups. The MIPIb score is calculated using the formula: [0.03535 x age (years)] + 0.6978 (if ECOG > 1) + [1.367 x log10(LDH/ULN)] + [0.9393 x log10(WBC count)] + [0.02142 x Ki-67 (%)]. A score < 5.7 indicates low risk disease, 5.7 - 6.5 indicates intermediate risk, and 6.5 or greater high risk.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form

DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to indicate the pathologic and/or clinical changes that result from treatment observed in a malignant tumor which originated in either the esophagus or gastroesophageal junction.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Malignant Neoplasm Regional Lymph Node Disease Response Status
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to indicate the pathologic and/or clinical changes that result from treatment observed in a malignant tumor(s) located in a regional lymph node(s).
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Intervention or Procedure Acute Respiratory Distress Syndrome Acute Lung Injury Occurrence Ind
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to indicate whether or not an incident occurred in which there was a progressive and life-threatening pulmonary distress in the absence of an underlying pulmonary condition or a finding of acute onset of bilateral pulmonary infiltrates by chest radiograph and a PaO2/FiO2 of less than or equal to 300, in the absence of heart failure, during or as a result of an intervention or a procedure.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Study Site Confirmation Intervention or Procedure Payment Or Insurance Clinical Trial Eligibility Criteria Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response to questions which are necessary to allow a subject to participate in a clinical study that address site confirmation of payments or insurance, as outlined in the study protocol, for an activity that produces an effect or intended to alter the course of a disease in a patient or population.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Intervention or Procedure Payment Or Insurance Confirmation Receive Clinical Trial Eligibility Criteria Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response to questions which are necessary to allow a subject to participate in a clinical study that address the confirmation of receipt for payments or insurance, as outlined in the study protocol, for an activity that produces an effect or intended to alter the course of a disease in a patient or population.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Diagnosis Biopsy Confirmation Ind
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to indicate whether or not the diagnosis of a disease, condition, or injury was verified via a microscopic examination of tissue specimens or fluid removed from the living body.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Oligometastasis Present Ind
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to indicate whether or not a type of metastasis in which cancer cells from the original (primary) tumor travel through the body and form a small number of new tumors (metastatic tumors) in one or two other parts of the body is present.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Imaging Technique Chest X-Ray Performed Ind
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to indicate whether or not an x-ray examination of the chest for use in screening, diagnosis, surgical procedures or therapy was completed.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Imaging Technique Chest X-Ray Performed Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to indicated the date on which an x-ray examination of the chest for use in screening, diagnosis, surgical procedures or therapy was completed.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Head and Neck CT Scan Performed Ind
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to indicate whether or not a method of examining an area of the body generally construed to comprise the base of skull and facial bones, sinuses, orbits, salivary glands, oral cavity, oropharynx, larynx, thyroid, facial and neck musculature and lymph nodes draining these areas by scanning them with X rays and using a computer to construct a series of cross-sectional scans along a single axis was completed.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Head and Neck CT Scan Performed Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to indicated the date on which a method of examining an area of the body generally construed to comprise the base of skull and facial bones, sinuses, orbits, salivary glands, oral cavity, oropharynx, larynx, thyroid, facial and neck musculature and lymph nodes draining these areas by scanning them with X rays and using a computer to construct a series of cross-sectional scans along a single axis was completed.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chromosomal Abnormality Stratification Factors Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine the selected pre-treatment factors by which patients are segregated to assure equal balance of these factors before randomization to the intervention arms of a clinical protocol based on an irregularity in the number or structure of chromosomes, usually in the form of a gain (duplication), loss (deletion), exchange (translocation), or alteration in sequence (inversion) of genetic material.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Bilateral Oophorectomy Occurrence Clinical Trial Eligibility Criteria Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The indicator to address the surgical removal of both ovaries, as outlined in the study protocol, to determine patient eligibility for clinical trial participation.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Bilateral Oophorectomy Occurrence Age Number
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The number that represents the age when surgical removal of both ovaries occurred.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Endometrial Ablation Occurrence Age Number

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Endometrial Ablation Occurrence Clinical Trial Eligibility Criteria Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The indicator to address endometrial ablation therapy, as outlined in the study protocol, to determine patient eligibility for clinical trial participation.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Breast Benign Biopsy Diagnosis Clinical Trial Eligibility Criteria Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The indicator to address benign biopsy results of the breast, as outlined in the study protocol, to determine patient eligibility for clinical trial participation.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Imaging Technique Research Activity Clinical Study Consent Ind-3
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine whether permission was given to conduct a systemic investigation using technology or method that aids in the visualization of any biological process, cell, tissue or organ for use in screening, diagnosis, surgical procedures or therapy in order to discover facts, establish or revise a theory, or develop a plan of action based on the facts discovered or a clinical trial site is not participating due to lack of credentialing.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: New Primary Malignant Neoplasm Or MDS Diagnosed Ind
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine whether or not a malignant tumor at the original site of growth or a clonal hematopoietic disorder characterized by dysplasia and ineffective hematopoiesis in one or more of the hematopoietic cell lines which did not previously exist was diagnosed.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Created for Notice of NPT and New Primary Form, 02/01/2019 JG

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Clinical Trial Eligibility Criteria Current Fulfill Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The indicator as to whether the patient meets eligibility criteria at the present time.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Malignant Neoplasm Clinical Trial Eligibility Criteria Stage
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The indicator to determine eligibility for clinical trial participation for questions related to the extent of a cancer in the patient's body as outlined in the study protocol.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient ECOG Performance Status Or Trial Screening Health Care Provider Ineligibility Decision Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The indicator to address the patient's ECOG performance status or ineligibility decided by persons licensed to supply health care.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Questionnaire Language Preference Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The indicator to address the patient's preferred language for questionnaires.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Healthcare Activity Facility Clinical Trial Eligibility Criteria Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The indicator to determine eligibility for clinical trial participation for questions related to the patient's healthcare at a facility as outlined in the study protocol.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Number of Pack Years Smoked History Stratification Factors Category
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine the selected pre-treatment factors by which patients are segregated to assure equal balance of these factors before randomization to the intervention arms of a clinical protocol based on the measurement of the amount of smoking exposure an individual has had over time.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Verbal Consent Obtained Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Response that indicates whether permission to do something was verbally obtained.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Verbal Consent Obtained Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date when permission to do something was verbally obtained.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Malignant Neoplasm Diagnosis Type Text

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Pneumonitis Severity Stratification Factors Grade
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine the selected pre-treatment factors by which patients are segregated to assure equal balance of these factors before randomization to the intervention arms of a clinical protocol based on the severity of inflammation affecting the lung parenchyma.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Potential Study Subject For Clinical Trial Participation Ind
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine whether or not a living individual who, due to the possession of one or more characteristics such e.g. as a particular medical condition specific to the study, is pre-qualified as a prospective study subject in a research study that prospectively assigns human participants or groups of humans to one or more health-related interventions to evaluate the effects on health outcomes.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Molecular Based Risk Factor Clinical Trial Stratification Status
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine the selected pre-treatment factors by which patients are segregated to assure equal balance of these factors before randomization to the intervention arms of a clinical protocol founded on molecules that increases the chance of developing a disease.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Lenalidomide Maintenance Therapy Dose
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine the quantity of lenalidomide previously given during the continuation of treatment for an extended period of time to prevent relapse.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Serum Or Urine M Protein Present Ind
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine whether or not aprotein complex comprised of two heavy chains and two light chains (monoclonal immunoglobulin/m protein) is found in the clear liquid part of the blood that remains after blood cells and clotting proteins have been removed and/or in the fluid that is excreted by the kidneys.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Diagnosis Biopsy Confirmation Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to indicate whether the diagnosis of a disease, condition, or injury was verified via a microscopic examination of tissue specimens or fluid removed from the living body.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine degree of abnormality of cancer cells, a measure of differentiation, the extent to which cancer cells are similar in appearance and function to healthy cells of the same tissue type.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Clinical Laboratory Evaluation Program Specimen Testing Approval Obtained Ind
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine whether approval of a procedure(s) for critical evaluation of a preparation of tissue or bodily fluid taken for examination or diagnosis was obtained from a program of the New York State Department of Health that administers the activities of the Clinical Laboratory Reference System and provides the oversight of over 1,000 clinical laboratories and blood banks, including out-of-state facilities that accept clinical specimens collected in New York State called Clinical Laboratory Evaluation Program (CLEP).
DataElementQueryResults.origin: ECOG CRF:Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Case Report Form

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Non-Protocol Therapy Administered Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine the type of non-protocol therapy given.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Additional New Primary Tumor To Report Ind
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine whether there is an additional finding indicating the development of a tumor in a patient with a history of a previously diagnosed tumor with a different histopathologic profile in another anatomic site as compared to the most recent one to report.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Interest Pregnancy Within One Year Occurrence Ind
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine whether a person is interested in becoming pregnant within one year of an event.
